  "title": "Governance & Administration, Exec/Senior Executive/ Principal Executive/Assistant Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Scope:</strong><br />The Governance & Administration (GA) team will develop and maintain effective governance and efficient processes for the industry funds, grant schemes, programmes, and MOUs.</p><p>As part of the GA team, your key duties and responsibilities include:</p><ul><li>To process grant claims and disbursements, including checking of documentations and clarification with grant applicants and project managers, issuance of offer letters, etc.</li></ul><ul><li>To assist GA team in data collection and reporting to senior management and stakeholders.</li></ul><ul><li>To support the division’s finance/budgeting and procurement functions, as well as providing administrative and logistics support to the division. Examples of such responsibilities are calendar management, assisting in organising of meetings/events, supporting division’s knowledge management, and system access management.</li></ul><p>You will also play a supporting role in the,</p><ul><li>Review and implement policies, guidelines, SOPs, and templates that enhance the division’s objectives and processes.</li></ul><ul><li>Report and present KPIs of division’s industry funds to the client's Board, SMM and stakeholders.</li></ul><ul><li>Develop and manage division’s grant management system and anomaly/fraud detection system.</li></ul><ul><li>Recommend and source for external funds that the client could leverage for industry development</li></ul><ul><li>Conduct industry consultation, surveys and interviews relating to the industry funds.</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Min. Diploma</li><li>Relevant or applicable experience in grant claims and disbursements. Some experience in <strong>government sector</strong> will be a plus. </li></ul><p><br /><strong>Working Arrangement:</strong></p><ul><li>8.30am to 6pm (Monday to Thursday), </li><li>8.30am to 5.00pm (Friday)</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Contract Duration:</strong> 1 year (Starting 1 Mar 2026)<br /><strong>Location</strong>: Marina South Pier<br /><strong>Salary: </strong>$5000 - $6000<br /></p><p>EA License No.: 96C4864 (Shanice Lim Xin Ni)<br />Reg. No.: R22110485</p>",
